(97, 1, '2017-02-26 03:50:34', '2017-02-26 03:50:34', '<h2 class="fl-heading" style="text-align: center;"><strong><span class="fl-heading-text">Mission Statement</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Purity Homes'' mission is to provide a simple and affordable solution for all New Zealanders to live and work in healthy, environmentally conscious and efficient buildings.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"><span class="fl-heading-text">Our Purpose</span></h3>\r\nPurity Homes was formed in 2011 with the purpose of providing you with an easy way to design and build a healthy home, without a big price tag. Most homes in New Zealand, old and new, are mouldy and toxic death boxes. We are here to change that. You now have the opportunity to live in a home that truly puts your health first. And we make the process simple and quick!\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"></h3>\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"><span class="fl-heading-text">Our Vision</span></h3>\r\nOur vision is not only for New Zealand, but for a world where everyone lives in a healthy home made from non-toxic and natural materials. We imagine a world where all building materials are renewable and have waste-stream management plans. A world where homes and offices look after the health and pockets of their occupants, and the wellbeing of nature.\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"></h3>\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"><span class="fl-heading-text">Background and Development</span></h3>\r\nOur team was formed out of mutual interest in creating something good, something meaningful and something which adds social value. It did not take long after the Christchurch earthquakes for us to identify that the rebuild provided opportunities for improving the NZ housing stock. With the combination of Guido’s upbringing in The Netherlands and Drew’s knowledge of the NZ building industry, it only took one or two discussions to decide that NZ needed some good energy put into bettering the health and performance of buildings. Thus Purity Homes was formed.\r\n\r\nAfter three years of worldwide research we joined forces with the developers of ForeverBreathe products and systems. Captivated by the ForeverBreathe teams’ shared energy and passion, we soon found ourselves tangled in the web of breathable building systems. Purity Homes has now secured a solid business model to deliver our core values and vision into NZ by enabling kiwis to design and build with a full Health Based building system.', 'about us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-26 03:50:34', '2017-02-26 03:50:34', '', 20, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2017-02-26 05:47:50', '2017-02-26 05:47:50', '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Foreverbreathe</strong>™ high performance breathable wall systems now provide architects, designers, manufacturers and the home owner with an alternative to traditional airtight construction methods. Advanced structural performance, stability, breathability, superior durability, increased indoor air quality and energy savings are but some of the performance benefits delivered. With an ever-increasing consumer interest in health based building and sustainable development, <strong>Foreverbreathe</strong>™ wall systems are well placed to answer the call.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class="fl-heading"><span class="fl-heading-text">Consider these facts</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The overwhelming majority of chemicals in built environments remain untested.</li>\r\n 	<li>The vogue strategy in the building industry of airtight shells and increasingly chemically-based construction materials, is broadly accepted throughout the industry.</li>\r\n 	<li>An ever increasing volume of nasty chemical encapsulated interior products, decorative coatings and high moisture levels are trapped within the airtight shell to form what is known as a chemical cocktail effect. An effect currently mitigated by energy sapping mechanical air movement systems and calculations that determine the total area included for opening windows.</li>\r\n 	<li>Indoor air quality has been estimated to be an average of 5-10 times more unhealthy than outside air (EPA, WHO).</li>\r\n 	<li>Building failures are on the increase with wall solutions failing within warranty periods.</li>\r\n 	<li>The airtight strategy and the value structure that supports it should be earnestly re-examined. There is a better way.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Foreverbreathe</strong>™ high performance wall system allows moisture vapour to exit the interior passing through the wool insulation where heat is retained through a thermodynamic process that keeps the inner wall dry.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">An effect currently mitigated by energy sapping mechanical air movement systems or a reliance on occupants to open windows and ventilate.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">As moisture is evaporated out of the wool fibre, energy is absorbed. Similarly, as moisture is absorbed into the wool fibre, energy is released.</p>', 'foreverbreathe', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-02-26 05:47:50', '2017-02-26 05:47:50', '', 28, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
