>\r\n 	<li>A landscaping plan is produced for the surrounding areas of the building</li>\r\n 	<li>A Quantity Survey is run on the building to quantify all materials</li>\r\n 	<li>The 3D textured CAD is updated to represent the final design</li>\r\n 	<li>Final plans are taken through consent with your local council</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOnce the consented plans are released by council you are ready to choose a construction firm and commence building.\r\n\r\nPurity Homes will provide you and the construction firm with ongoing support during and after the construction of your Health Based Building to ensure everything goes to plan.', 'Commercial', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-20 22:57:32', '2017-03-20 22:57:32', '', 181, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/181-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(183, 1, '2017-03-20 22:58:09', '2017-03-20 22:58:09', '<h4><strong>Preliminary stage</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>First we find out what your ideal Health Based Building home looks like in your mind. If you already have a section, we ask you to send through the site plan and recent pictures</li>\r\n 	<li>We will then ask for you to complete the short questionnaire at the end of this document. From these answers we can assess your project and propose how we can help</li>\r\n 	<li>An indication of price to build is presented based on the size and specifications of your new home</li>\r\n 	<li>Once we confirm that our offering is within your budget and requirements, we present to you our Design Services Contract which outlines the two stages of your project process in detail.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 1</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We gather your personal desires and requirements in fine detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you do not already have a site plan with levels and boundaries or geo-tech report for your property, we can connect you to a land surveyor. We are happy to add the service of organizing this to our offering</li>\r\n 	<li>A 3D textured CAD (Computer-Aided Design) is produced, modeling the proposed design on your property to give you a visual representation</li>\r\n 	<li>You can review the plan in your own time and request minor changes, or one complete re-design if you wish. Your design is then confirmed</li>\r\n 	<li>A site-specific technical plan is produced, positioning the services on your property, confirming the house position is within council regulations and identifying the foundation type appropriate for your section</li>\r\n 	<li>A preliminary engineering assessment is produced if necessary</li>\r\n 	<li>The site plan and CAD elevations are used to run a Project Information Memorandum (PIM) with your local council which prepares the design for consent</li>\r\n 	<li>We provide you with an in-house produced price estimate to build, comprising of a breakdown of primary materials and labour resulting in a per-square-metre estimate cost. This is an indicative price only</li>\r\n 	<li>A finalised price for Stage 2 is now presented</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe total fee for Stage 1 is <u>$3,700 + GST</u> based on any standard design requiring no additional engineering services.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 1 is inclusive of a PC sum of $600 +GST for the PIM. If the PIM exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 2</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We connect you with our partners to design and confirm your kitchen, bathrooms, heating and lighting options and make any changes to suit your preferences and budget. You will receive a specification sheet from these suppliers for us to include in your design specifications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Now is also the time for you to revisit the selections available for your timber floor, cladding and decking options via detailed product sheets and samples.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your specification and pricing sheets are updated with your specific product choices</li>\r\n 	<li>Working drawings are completed which are then taken through consent with your local council</li>\r\n 	<li>You are now provided with consented plans ready to build and can hand these plans to a builder of your choice. Their price to build will be based on their own internal pricing inclusive of labour and the material pricing sheet we have provided to you</li>\r\n 	<li>Purity Homes will provide you and your builder with ongoing support during and after the construction of your home to help ensure everything goes to plan</li>\r\n 	<li>You are given a Purity Homes welcome kit with all the details of your home including material details, maintenance guidelines and an EcoStore hamper</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Enjoy!</strong></h4>\r\nThe fee for Stage 2 is estimated at <u>$15,000 + GST</u> based on a single story design no larger than 250sqm on flat TC1 land. A confirmed price for Stage 2 will be presented upon the completion of Stage 1.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 2 is inclusive of a PC sum of $4,000 excl. GST for consenting and processing, if the council consenting exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>', 'Residential', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'residential', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '', 0, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/?p=183', 0, 'post', '', 0),
