(193, 1, '2017-03-21 04:22:19', '2017-03-21 04:22:19', '<h4><strong>Preliminary stage</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>First we find out what your ideal Health Based Building looks like in your mind. This will include a meeting or a phone call, following the information gathered from the questionnaire at the bottom of this page.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you already have a site secured, we ask you to send through the site plan and recent pictures. If needed, we connect you to a geotechnical engineer to have the land surveyed and soil tested.</li>\r\n 	<li>A basic 2D indicative floor plan are produced to ensure there is an understanding of what is required. This initial drawing will be the basis on which your final plans are produced in the following stages.</li>\r\n 	<li>An indication of price to build is presented based on the size and specifications of your Health Based Building</li>\r\n 	<li>Once we confirm that our offering is within your budget and requirements, we present to you our Design Services Contract which outlines the two stages of your project process in detail.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThis preliminary stage will incur no charge. The price for Stage 1 will be defined once this preliminary stage is completed and we have a thorough understanding of the project.\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 1</strong></h4>\r\nThe aim of this stage is to develop the design to a point where the basic structure and layout are understood and considered feasible to construct with an indicative cost to build.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The initial 2D design is fine tuned to meet your needs. If required, one full redesign is offered.</li>\r\n 	<li>Geotechnical results and the site survey are confirmed</li>\r\n 	<li>An early discussion is held with the local Council to highlight any unforeseen issues with the proposed build and identify requirements that may be of concern</li>\r\n 	<li>Structural, fire and civil engineers review the proposed design. Basic engineering calculations are made to ensure the structure can move forward. This also kick starts their final calculations.</li>\r\n 	<li>The plan is reviewed and if needed, minor changes are made.</li>\r\n 	<li>A site plan is produced with basic elevations, along with a feasibility report upon assessing council requirements and site information</li>\r\n 	<li>A basic textured 3D CAD is produced, modeling the proposed design on your property for a visual representation of your new facility</li>\r\n 	<li>The design information is run through a PIM (Project Information Memorandum) with the local council to highlight any issues with the proposed design and best ensure success when the building is submitted for consent</li>\r\n 	<li>If required, minor changes are made to the design based on the outcome of the PIM.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your proposed design is presented together with all documents collated and developed.</li>\r\n 	<li>The price for Stage 2 is now defined and is dependent on the complexity of the project.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nProgressing to Stage 2 is treated as a seperate contract to ensure your initial investment in a basic design and project assessment is low.\r\n\r\nIn the event that a full redesign is required as a result of the PIM report or otherwise, an assessment will be made if Stage 1 is better extended or restarted.\r\n\r\n<strong>Stage 2</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The commencement of Stage 2 will confirm that the main structure design and building layout is complete and finalised</li>\r\n 	<li>The design is reviewed by all engineers for a final assessment to ensure the building meets regulations</li>\r\n 	<li>A final working set of structural drawings are produced</li>\r\n 	<li>Cladding, interior lining and other aesthetic features are selected and finalised</li>\r\n 	<li>A draftsman produces a working set of drawings around the engineered structure to be taken to consent</li>\r\n 	<li>All specifications are cross-checked by all relevant professionals to to ensure the final set meets all requirements</li>\r\n 	<li>A landscaping plan is produced for the surrounding areas of the building</li>\r\n 	<li>A Quantity Survey is run on the building to quantify all materials</li>\r\n 	<li>The 3D textured CAD is updated to represent the final design</li>\r\n 	<li>Final plans are taken through consent with your local council</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOnce the consented plans are released by council you are ready to choose a construction firm and commence building.\r\n\r\nPurity Homes will provide you and the construction firm with ongoing support during and after the construction of your Health Based Building to ensure everything goes to plan.', 'Commercial', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-21 04:22:19', '2017-03-21 04:22:19', '', 181, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/181-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
