(211, 1, '2017-03-21 04:41:34', '2017-03-21 04:41:34', '<h2 style="text-align: center;">Using timber in construction can be very unsustainable, or in the case of Foreverbeech™, very sustainably.</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">It can also be very unhealthy when treated with toxic chemicals for durability, or in the case of Foreverbeech, durable in itself and no requirement for chemical treatments. New Zealand beech harvested from the West Coast of New Zealand by industry-leading firm New Zealand Sustainable Forestry Products (NZSFP), is the number one option for sustainably sourced hardwood. It''s forest management practices are second to none, as documented by the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organisation (<a href="http://www.fao.org/docrep/007/ae542e/ae542e00.htm">click here</a>), Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry (<a href="http://www.foreverbeech.co.nz/app_docs/confirmation_of_sustainable_forest_mngmt_maf_2010-05-11.pdf">click here</a>) and Ministry of Primary Industries (MPI).</p>', 'foreverbeech', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '79-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-03-21 04:41:34', '2017-03-21 04:41:34', '', 79, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/79-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
