(380, 1, '2017-04-09 23:43:22', '2017-04-09 23:43:22', '<div class="col-md-6"><img class="wp-image-298" style="margin: 20px 0;" src="http://www.purityhomes.co.nzwp-content/uploads/2017/04/FBEF_Slider_675x270_2.jpg" alt="Foreverbeech flooring, Purity Homes" width="500" height="200" /><img class="wp-image-300" style="margin: 20px 0;" src="http://www.purityhomes.co.nzwp-content/uploads/2017/04/FBEF_Bevel_420-1.jpg" alt="Foreverbeech flooring, Purity Homes" width="500" height="102" /><a class="btn btn-green btn-block" href="http://www.hardie-thomson.co.nz/site/hardieandthomson/images/Flooring/flooringdownloads/NZS0103_Beech%20Engineered%20Floor_HT_v6-web.pdf" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-download"></i> Download Product Sheet</a></div>\r\n<div class="col-md-6"><img class="alignnone wp-image-304" style="margin: 20px 0;" src="http://www.purityhomes.co.nzwp-content/uploads/2017/04/FBSTF_Slider_675x270.jpg" alt="Foreverbeech solid flooring, Purity Homes" width="500" height="200" /><img class="alignnone wp-image-303" style="margin: 20px 0;" src="http://www.purityhomes.co.nzwp-content/uploads/2017/04/FBSTF_Bevel_420.jpg" alt="Foreverbeech flooring, Purity Homes" width="500" height="120" /><a class="btn btn-green btn-block" href="http://www.hardie-thomson.co.nz/site/hardieandthomson/NZS0123_Solid%20Timber%20Flooring%20-%20Product%20Sheet.pdf" target="_blank"><i class="fa fa-download"></i> Download Product Sheet</a></div>', 'Foreverbeech Flooring Products', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:43:22', '2017-04-09 23:43:22', '', 297, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(381, 1, '2017-04-09 23:44:04', '2017-04-09 23:44:04', '<strong>Weatherboard</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Magnum Weatherboard System is designed to provide homeowners with a high performance and sustainable cladding option without sacrificing appearance or affordability. It is particularly suitable for use with other breathable building materials, such as the Foreverbreathe wall system.', 'Magnum Board Weatherboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '239-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:44:04', '2017-04-09 23:44:04', '', 239, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/239-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(382, 1, '2017-04-09 23:44:21', '2017-04-09 23:44:21', '<strong>Wall Lining</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Magnum Board Interior Wall Lining system is designed to be versatile with high performance in all areas of the home. Entirely breathable and non-toxic, it can also be used in wet areas, as a bracing element, fire-protection, and is certainly hard enough to withstand a few bumps and knocks. All in all, it''s good for just about everywhere!', 'Magnum Board Wall Lining', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '233-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:44:21', '2017-04-09 23:44:21', '', 233, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/233-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(383, 1, '2017-04-09 23:44:33', '2017-04-09 23:44:33', '<strong>Rigid Air Barrier</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Magnum Board Rigid Air Barrier system is to be used over framing prior to cladding installation, for use in wind zones up to and including ‘extra -high’ as defined by NZS3604.\r\n\r\nIt is designed to provide seamless weather-proofing and wind resistant protection of wall framing.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.hardie-thomson.co.nz/site/hardieandthomson/images/FBreatheDownloads/Magnum%20Board%20Rigid%20Air%20Barrier%20and%20Weather%20Board%20Technical%20Manual%2025052016.pdf" target="_blank">Download Manual</a>', 'Magnum Board Rigid Air Barrier', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '224-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:44:33', '2017-04-09 23:44:33', '', 224, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/224-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(384, 1, '2017-04-09 23:44:56', '2017-04-09 23:44:56', '<h4><strong>Preliminary stage</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>First we find out what your ideal Health Based Building home looks like in your mind. If you already have a section, we ask you to send through the site plan and recent pictures</li>\r\n 	<li>We will then ask for you to complete the short questionnaire at the end of this document. From these answers we can assess your project and propose how we can help</li>\r\n 	<li>An indication of price to build is presented based on the size and specifications of your new home</li>\r\n 	<li>Once we confirm that our offering is within your budget and requirements, we present to you our Design Services Contract which outlines the two stages of your project process in detail.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 1</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We gather your personal desires and requirements in fine detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you do not already have a site plan with levels and boundaries or geo-tech report for your property, we can connect you to a land surveyor. We are happy to add the service of organizing this to our offering</li>\r\n 	<li>A 3D textured CAD (Computer-Aided Design) is produced, modeling the proposed design on your property to give you a visual representation</li>\r\n 	<li>You can review the plan in your own time and request minor changes, or one complete re-design if you wish. Your design is then confirmed</li>\r\n 	<li>A site-specific technical plan is produced, positioning the services on your property, confirming the house position is within council regulations and identifying the foundation type appropriate for your section</li>\r\n 	<li>A preliminary engineering assessment is produced if necessary</li>\r\n 	<li>The site plan and CAD elevations are used to run a Project Information Memorandum (PIM) with your local council which prepares the design for consent</li>\r\n 	<li>We provide you with an in-house produced price estimate to build, comprising of a breakdown of primary materials and labour resulting in a per-square-metre estimate cost. This is an indicative price only</li>\r\n 	<li>A finalised price for Stage 2 is now presented</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe total fee for Stage 1 is <u>$3,700 + GST</u> based on any standard design requiring no additional engineering services.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 1 is inclusive of a PC sum of $600 +GST for the PIM. If the PIM exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 2</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We connect you with our partners to design and confirm your kitchen, bathrooms, heating and lighting options and make any changes to suit your preferences and budget. You will receive a specification sheet from these suppliers for us to include in your design specifications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Now is also the time for you to revisit the selections available for your timber floor, cladding and decking options via detailed product sheets and samples.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your specification and pricing sheets are updated with your specific product choices</li>\r\n 	<li>Working drawings are completed which are then taken through consent with your local council</li>\r\n 	<li>You are now provided with consented plans ready to build and can hand these plans to a builder of your choice. Their price to build will be based on their own internal pricing inclusive of labour and the material pricing sheet we have provided to you</li>\r\n 	<li>Purity Homes will provide you and your builder with ongoing support during and after the construction of your home to help ensure everything goes to plan</li>\r\n 	<li>You are given a Purity Homes welcome kit with all the details of your home including material details, maintenance guidelines and an EcoStore hamper</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Enjoy!</strong></h4>\r\nThe fee for Stage 2 is estimated at <u>$15,000 + GST</u> based on a single story design no larger than 250sqm on flat TC1 land. A confirmed price for Stage 2 will be presented upon the completion of Stage 1.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 2 is inclusive of a PC sum of $4,000 excl. GST for consenting and processing, if the council consenting exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>', 'Our Services Residential', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:44:56', '2017-04-09 23:44:56', '', 183, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(385, 1, '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '<h4><strong>Preliminary stage</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>First we find out what your ideal Health Based Building home looks like in your mind. If you already have a section, we ask you to send through the site plan and recent pictures</li>\r\n 	<li>We will then ask for you to complete the short questionnaire at the end of this document. From these answers we can assess your project and propose how we can help</li>\r\n 	<li>An indication of price to build is presented based on the size and specifications of your new home</li>\r\n 	<li>Once we confirm that our offering is within your budget and requirements, we present to you our Design Services Contract which outlines the two stages of your project process in detail.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 1</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We gather your personal desires and requirements in fine detail.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you do not already have a site plan with levels and boundaries or geo-tech report for your property, we can connect you to a land surveyor. We are happy to add the service of organizing this to our offering</li>\r\n 	<li>A 3D textured CAD (Computer-Aided Design) is produced, modeling the proposed design on your property to give you a visual representation</li>\r\n 	<li>You can review the plan in your own time and request minor changes, or one complete re-design if you wish. Your design is then confirmed</li>\r\n 	<li>A site-specific technical plan is produced, positioning the services on your property, confirming the house position is within council regulations and identifying the foundation type appropriate for your section</li>\r\n 	<li>A preliminary engineering assessment is produced if necessary</li>\r\n 	<li>The site plan and CAD elevations are used to run a Project Information Memorandum (PIM) with your local council which prepares the design for consent</li>\r\n 	<li>We provide you with an in-house produced price estimate to build, comprising of a breakdown of primary materials and labour resulting in a per-square-metre estimate cost. This is an indicative price only</li>\r\n 	<li>A finalised price for Stage 2 is now presented</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe total fee for Stage 1 is <u>$3,700 + GST</u> based on any standard design requiring no additional engineering services.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 1 is inclusive of a PC sum of $600 +GST for the PIM. If the PIM exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>\r\n<h4><strong>Stage 2</strong></h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>We connect you with our partners to design and confirm your kitchen, bathrooms, heating and lighting options and make any changes to suit your preferences and budget. You will receive a specification sheet from these suppliers for us to include in your design specifications.</li>\r\n 	<li>Now is also the time for you to revisit the selections available for your timber floor, cladding and decking options via detailed product sheets and samples.</li>\r\n 	<li>Your specification and pricing sheets are updated with your specific product choices</li>\r\n 	<li>Working drawings are completed which are then taken through consent with your local council</li>\r\n 	<li>You are now provided with consented plans ready to build and can hand these plans to a builder of your choice. Their price to build will be based on their own internal pricing inclusive of labour and the material pricing sheet we have provided to you</li>\r\n 	<li>Purity Homes will provide you and your builder with ongoing support during and after the construction of your home to help ensure everything goes to plan</li>\r\n 	<li>You are given a Purity Homes welcome kit with all the details of your home including material details, maintenance guidelines and an EcoStore hamper</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4><strong>Enjoy!</strong></h4>\r\nThe fee for Stage 2 is estimated at <u>$15,000 + GST</u> based on a single story design no larger than 250sqm on flat TC1 land. A confirmed price for Stage 2 will be presented upon the completion of Stage 1.\r\n\r\n<em>* Stage 2 is inclusive of a PC sum of $4,000 excl. GST for consenting and processing, if the council consenting exceeds this cost, evidence will be provided and the extra cost will be directly billable to the client</em>', 'Residential', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '2017-04-09 23:45:10', '', 183, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(386, 1, '2017-04-10 01:12:29', '2017-04-10 01:12:29', '<h2 class="fl-heading" style="text-align: center;">Purity Homes'' mission is to provide a simple and affordable solution for all New Zealanders to live and work in healthy, environmentally conscious and efficient buildings.</h2>\r\n<p class="fl-heading"></p>', 'about us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-10 01:12:29', '2017-04-10 01:12:29', '', 20, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(387, 1, '2017-04-10 01:12:57', '2017-04-10 01:12:57', '<p class="fl-heading"><strong><span class="fl-heading-text">Our Purpose</span></strong></p>\r\nPurity Homes was formed in 2011 with the purpose of providing you with an easy way to design and build a healthy home, without a big price tag. Most homes in New Zealand, old and new, are mouldy and toxic death boxes. We are here to change that. You now have the opportunity to live in a home that truly puts your health first. And we make the process simple and quick!\r\n<p class="fl-heading"><strong><span class="fl-heading-text">Our Vision</span></strong></p>\r\nOur vision is not only for New Zealand, but for a world where everyone lives in a healthy home made from non-toxic and natural materials. We imagine a world where all building materials are renewable and have waste-stream management plans. A world where homes and offices look after the health and pockets of their occupants, and the wellbeing of nature.\r\n<p class="fl-heading"> <strong><span class="fl-heading-text">Background and Development</span></strong></p>\r\nOur team was formed out of mutual interest in creating something good, something meaningful and something which adds social value. It did not take long after the Christchurch earthquakes for us to identify that the rebuild provided opportunities for improving the NZ housing stock. With the combination of Guido’s upbringing in The Netherlands and Drew’s knowledge of the NZ building industry, it only took one or two discussions to decide that NZ needed some good energy put into bettering the health and performance of buildings. Thus Purity Homes was formed.\r\n\r\nAfter three years of worldwide research we joined forces with the developers of ForeverBreathe products and systems. Captivated by the ForeverBreathe teams’ shared energy and passion, we soon found ourselves tangled in the web of breathable building systems. Purity Homes has now secured a solid business model to deliver our core values and vision into NZ by enabling kiwis to design and build with a full Health Based building system.', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2017-04-10 01:12:57', '2017-04-10 01:12:57', '', 0, 'http://www.purityhomes.co.nz/?p=387', 0, 'post', '', 0),
